flowRoot.flowPara: Set your leading, commonly known of as line-height, to 120–145% of your base font size. Give your words room to breath.
One or two, but not a slew. Regular, bold, and italic variants are essential; OpenType features and multiple weights give your typography class.
For print, 10–14 pt is recommended; on screen, 16–24 px for body text

text.tspan: Serif: Linux Libertine, Alegreya, Droid Serif
Sans-serif: Lato, Ubuntu, Fira Sans, Roboto

flowRoot.flowPara: Large blocks of text are harder to read. Aim for 4o–90 char­ac­ters per line. This is 40.
Everything should look in place. Ideally, use a grid and typographic scale. Align body text left.
